********************************************************************
  			 MAKE FILE
********************************************************************

For each of NoCombiner, Combiner, In Map Combine, Secondary Sort,
makefile expects input file(s) to be placed in the "input" folder
that is present in the same directory as makefile.

makefile has two tasks:
	a) run: to build the jar
	b) local: to execute the jar with required input & output paths

"make" would build the jar
"make local" would execute the jar 
